&lt;p&gt;We require an active Healthcare Support Worker to join the dedicated Leg Ulcer Nursing team as the service expands and develops across Dorset. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be required to implement nursing care for patients under the supervision of a Specialist Leg Ulcer Nurse and work in partnership with the clients and their carers enabling them to make informed choices.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is for 15 hours per week Tuesdays and Thursdays supporting Level 3 Complex Leg Ulcer Service. Level 3 Complex Leg Ulcer Service comprises of clinic assessment, Home visits, Care/Nursing Homes visits and Community Hospital visits across West and parts of North Dorset. There will also be ample opportunity to work within the service on the bank to cover annual leave and sickness. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;On-going support and training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
